00:03:52.860 --> 00:03:57.010
but really the order that I kind
of approach the app when I'm

00:03:57.030 --> 00:03:59.860
doing one of the UI reviews,
such as, you know,

00:03:59.860 --> 00:04:01.740
we've got the UI design
lab on the third floor.

00:04:01.740 --> 00:04:02.960
Please go and check that out.

00:04:03.140 --> 00:04:05.670
And so when I go through these apps
with the developers one-on-one,

00:04:05.670 --> 00:04:08.840
it starts with the first impression,
then kind of playing around with the

00:04:08.840 --> 00:04:12.340
different features and learning a little
bit more about what they're trying to do,

00:04:12.340 --> 00:04:13.560
what users want to do.

00:04:13.560 --> 00:04:16.340
And so that's kind of the order that
I'm going to go through these pitfalls.

00:04:16.360 --> 00:04:18.220
Okay, so let's get started.

00:04:18.220 --> 00:04:22.150
And the first pitfall I want
to talk about is bad app icons.

00:04:22.160 --> 00:04:25.600
You guys are all probably seen
lots of apps with bad app icons.

00:04:25.600 --> 00:04:29.020
And you know that an app icon is really
the first impression that users are

00:04:29.020 --> 00:04:32.070
going to have of your whole product,
your whole experience.

00:04:32.140 --> 00:04:33.940
It's the first thing
they're going to see.

00:04:33.940 --> 00:04:35.480
They're going to judge
your app right away.

00:04:35.480 --> 00:04:38.820
And if you don't have a great app icon,
they're just not going to assume.

00:04:38.820 --> 00:04:42.820
They're going to assume that you also
have great features or a great UI.

00:04:42.890 --> 00:04:46.580
So here we're looking at the App Store,
and this is if you do

00:04:46.580 --> 00:04:48.820
a search for recipes.

00:04:48.820 --> 00:04:52.000
And I bet many of you right away,
right just looking at the screen,

00:04:52.050 --> 00:04:53.800
are starting to make judgments.

00:04:53.820 --> 00:04:56.820
You're starting to say, well,
that app looks kind of interesting.

00:04:56.820 --> 00:04:58.600
These other ones, you know,
I don't know if I'm

00:04:58.680 --> 00:04:59.820
going to check that out.

00:04:59.820 --> 00:05:01.820
You know,
the App Store is so competitive now.

00:05:01.820 --> 00:05:03.820
And this is where it all begins.

00:05:03.820 --> 00:05:05.720
This is where the experience starts.

00:05:06.240 --> 00:05:08.810
This is before anybody's
read any of the reviews,

00:05:08.810 --> 00:05:12.640
seen the ratings, seen the screenshots,
heard about any of the features.

00:05:12.770 --> 00:05:14.840
This is just the app icon.

00:05:14.990 --> 00:05:17.960
So I think it kind of goes
without saying that an app,

00:05:18.090 --> 00:05:22.030
great app icon can play a huge
part in the success of your app.

00:05:23.100 --> 00:05:26.650
And so, of course, app icons,
just like all graphics in your app,

00:05:26.820 --> 00:05:28.000
need to be beautiful.

00:05:28.000 --> 00:05:30.420
It kind of goes without saying.

00:05:30.720 --> 00:05:33.050
But an app icon has some
extra responsibility.

00:05:33.160 --> 00:05:36.840
An app icon also needs to
be instantly recognizable.

00:05:36.930 --> 00:05:40.160
And that's really important because
a user is going to interact with your

00:05:40.160 --> 00:05:42.140
app icon not just on their home screen.

00:05:42.140 --> 00:05:45.920
They're going to first see it on the
iTunes store at various different sizes,

00:05:45.930 --> 00:05:47.650
depending on what device they're using.

00:05:47.780 --> 00:05:52.090
They're also going to see it in places
like Spotlight or inside of a folder or

00:05:52.090 --> 00:05:54.250
in settings or a notification center.

00:05:54.350 --> 00:05:56.790
And you need to make sure that when
you're designing an app icon that it

00:05:56.790 --> 00:05:59.200
works well at all these different sizes.

00:05:59.300 --> 00:06:01.880
And so to help you do that,
to make sure that your app icons are both

00:06:01.960 --> 00:06:04.770
beautiful and instantly recognizable,
I'm going to go through

00:06:04.770 --> 00:06:05.810
some tips right now.

00:06:05.930 --> 00:06:09.550
So the first tip is just to make sure
that you're focusing on a unique shape.

00:06:09.640 --> 00:06:14.000
If your app icon just has too many
shapes or too complicated of a shape,

00:06:14.060 --> 00:06:16.700
it's just going to be really
hard to distinguish at that small

00:06:16.830 --> 00:06:17.900
size that a user might see it.

00:06:17.900 --> 00:06:19.320
It will get all muddied up.

00:06:19.430 --> 00:06:21.660
And it's just not going
to be that memorable.

00:06:21.740 --> 00:06:24.300
So some of these app icons
you're probably familiar with.

00:06:24.370 --> 00:06:26.860
And I think you can see that
they're really great app icons,

00:06:26.860 --> 00:06:29.840
but the thing that jumps
out at you is the shape.

00:06:29.840 --> 00:06:33.080
That's kind of what really
grabs a user's attention.

00:06:33.190 --> 00:06:34.740
And there are subtle details in them.

00:06:34.740 --> 00:06:37.320
There's really nice textures,
kind of the fold of the paper,

00:06:37.390 --> 00:06:40.080
all these great details.

00:06:40.170 --> 00:06:43.200
But that's kind of
supporting that basic shape.

00:06:43.300 --> 00:06:45.850
And so what you really want to do is
make sure that that shape is there,

00:06:45.850 --> 00:06:48.990
and then you're building in around that.

00:06:49.220 --> 00:06:50.260
The same thing with colors.

00:06:50.260 --> 00:06:52.100
You need to make sure that
you're carefully selecting

00:06:52.100 --> 00:06:53.740
the colors in your app icon.

00:06:53.740 --> 00:06:56.590
It's best to stick with
a limited color palette.

00:06:56.900 --> 00:07:01.540
Maybe just two or three colors that
will really drive home your app icon.

00:07:01.540 --> 00:07:04.110
Use the colors from your brand,
maybe some colors from

00:07:04.480 --> 00:07:06.700
the interface elements,
or if you're trying to

00:07:06.700 --> 00:07:09.860
represent a physical object,
try to do that in a simple way.

00:07:10.920 --> 00:07:13.590
Now you can see here there's
a bunch of app icons,

00:07:13.590 --> 00:07:15.530
great use of color,
but it's really just a

00:07:15.540 --> 00:07:17.660
couple of them that pop out,
even though with

00:07:17.660 --> 00:07:21.060
Instagram there's that rainbow,
but it's really just the dark

00:07:21.070 --> 00:07:24.860
shades of brown and then that dark
lens that really create the shape

00:07:24.860 --> 00:07:26.940
and the colors for this app icon.

00:07:27.320 --> 00:07:28.640
So it's really important
that you do that.

00:07:28.650 --> 00:07:32.010
If you just have too many colors, again,
it's going to get too muddied

00:07:32.010 --> 00:07:35.160
up at all those different sizes
that a user might see them.

00:07:39.150 --> 00:07:42.300
You also want to make sure that you
avoid using a photo for your app icon.

00:07:42.310 --> 00:07:44.960
Photos are too visually distracting.

00:07:44.960 --> 00:07:48.660
It's hard to have a simplified
set of colors and it's hard to

00:07:48.810 --> 00:07:50.910
have a very well-defined shape.

00:07:51.090 --> 00:07:54.000
Let's say you were
building an astronomy app.

00:07:54.010 --> 00:07:57.250
It would be really tempting to
use this great photo here of the

00:07:57.250 --> 00:08:00.000
Milky Way and take this photo,
turn it into an app icon.

00:08:00.000 --> 00:08:03.000
I think it looks okay at this large size.

00:08:03.000 --> 00:08:07.000
But the user that downloads this is
someone that's really into astronomy.

00:08:07.000 --> 00:08:09.000
They've got a bunch of different
apps that are like this.

00:08:09.000 --> 00:08:11.000
This is not going to be that memorable.

00:08:11.000 --> 00:08:14.230
And at the smaller sizes,
it's really just going to turn

00:08:14.350 --> 00:08:18.000
into this bluish-purple object
that isn't that symbolic.

00:08:18.000 --> 00:08:21.620
So instead, really try to focus on some
details that you can enhance,

00:08:21.690 --> 00:08:22.820
simplify the colors.

00:08:23.250 --> 00:08:28.000
And that's exactly what the designers
of the Star Walk app icon did.

00:08:28.000 --> 00:08:31.980
So they really just took that hue,
the purple-bluish hue, simplified it.

00:08:33.000 --> 00:08:36.000
They simplified it down and then
they focused on the constellation.

00:08:36.010 --> 00:08:39.030
And this is a great app and they
really wanted to make sure the app

00:08:39.030 --> 00:08:43.000
icon represented and created this
really symbolic branding element.

00:08:43.000 --> 00:08:47.000
This is an app that actually won
the Apple Design Award in 2010.

00:08:47.020 --> 00:08:51.000
And so really try to think about what
is that object that you can really focus

00:08:51.000 --> 00:08:54.440
in and highlight and what are the colors
around it that you can kind of just

00:08:54.440 --> 00:08:58.000
really simplify and really focus on.

00:08:58.390 --> 00:09:01.960
Okay, the next tip is avoid
using a lot of text.

00:09:02.020 --> 00:09:03.000
Text just typically is a
little bit more complex.

00:09:03.000 --> 00:09:04.990
It's too hard to read at
all the different sizes.

00:09:05.000 --> 00:09:07.620
But on top of that,
the app store is available in so many

00:09:07.620 --> 00:09:10.000
different countries around the world now.

00:09:10.000 --> 00:09:11.940
And if you've got a lot
of text in your app icon,

00:09:12.010 --> 00:09:14.390
you're just kind of telling
those other countries that,

00:09:14.390 --> 00:09:17.970
you know, this may not be the type
of experience for me.

00:09:18.000 --> 00:09:20.000
This is, you know, maybe for that region.

00:09:20.000 --> 00:09:23.340
And you don't want to cut off access to
all these different customers and all

00:09:23.340 --> 00:09:27.000
these potential markets to make -- that
your app icon could be available in.

00:09:27.000 --> 00:09:30.310
And so I just want to kind of illustrate
the first point of just how hard

00:09:30.310 --> 00:09:32.000
it is to read text in an app icon.

00:09:32.000 --> 00:09:34.000
So I want to bring up a graphic here.

00:09:34.000 --> 00:09:36.950
Here we're looking at Fuzz
Hair and Makeup Studio.

00:09:37.000 --> 00:09:39.340
This is, you know,
a graphic that's probably

00:09:39.340 --> 00:09:42.760
designed for a beauty salon,
maybe their websites or maybe their,

00:09:42.760 --> 00:09:44.830
you know, actual signage in the store.

00:09:45.000 --> 00:09:47.000
And I think the graphic, you know,
looks okay.

00:09:47.000 --> 00:09:48.000
It's nice.

00:09:48.000 --> 00:09:48.970
There's nothing wrong with it.

00:09:49.070 --> 00:09:51.210
And so it would be tempting
to just take this graphic,

00:09:51.210 --> 00:09:53.970
their logo, their identity,
and just turn it into an app icon.

00:09:54.050 --> 00:09:57.000
That would be something that a lot
of people have done on the app store.

00:09:57.000 --> 00:09:58.850
You know,
it's the kind of easy thing to do,

00:09:59.000 --> 00:10:02.000
something that's memorable from people
that are going to the app store.

00:10:02.000 --> 00:10:04.740
And again,
it might look okay at this large size,

00:10:04.750 --> 00:10:08.000
at 5'12" or, you know,
even bigger than that.

00:10:08.000 --> 00:10:11.120
But it's not going to work well at
all the different sizes that a user

00:10:11.120 --> 00:10:13.000
is going to view it on their device.

00:10:13.000 --> 00:10:17.000
And you can kind of start to see what
happens when it gets really small.

00:10:17.000 --> 00:10:19.000
You just can't read any of the text.

00:10:19.000 --> 00:10:21.000
It kind of turns into
this blobby type of shape.

00:10:21.000 --> 00:10:23.000
It's just kind of white with colors.

00:10:23.000 --> 00:10:25.970
And it's just not really
effective as a good app icon.

00:10:26.000 --> 00:10:28.240
On the other hand,
there's some developers that

00:10:28.320 --> 00:10:31.000
have done some really great
stuff with their app icons.

00:10:31.000 --> 00:10:33.000
Here's an app called Quip.

00:10:33.000 --> 00:10:36.000
This is from Glasshouse
Apps in Australia.

00:10:36.020 --> 00:10:39.000
And this is a new Twitter client
that was just available on the iPad.

00:10:39.000 --> 00:10:41.000
Great app for catching
up on conversations.

00:10:41.000 --> 00:10:44.000
And so this is the logo
that they've got at the top.

00:10:44.000 --> 00:10:46.000
They designed this really nice logo,
Quip.

00:10:46.000 --> 00:10:48.000
It's got that Twitter bird in the queue.

00:10:48.000 --> 00:10:51.000
And so it would be tempting for
them to just take that logo again

00:10:51.000 --> 00:10:52.990
and then turn it into an app icon,
right?

00:10:53.000 --> 00:10:56.000
But it would look okay at this size.

00:10:56.000 --> 00:11:00.000
And again, it would start to really fall
apart at those smaller sizes.

00:11:00.000 --> 00:11:03.000
And so what they did was they
really focused on some key elements.

00:11:03.000 --> 00:11:05.800
How could we really emphasize
the shape so it's really

00:11:05.800 --> 00:11:08.000
distinguishable at all the sizes?

00:11:08.000 --> 00:11:11.000
And we still want to bring in the
colors from the branding elements

00:11:11.000 --> 00:11:13.890
because this is actually some of the
colors that they use in their app.

00:11:14.040 --> 00:11:16.990
And so what they did was they
focused in on just the bird's head.

00:11:17.000 --> 00:11:19.000
And it really created this nice shape.

00:11:19.000 --> 00:11:21.000
Used those colors, like I mentioned,
from the UI.

00:11:21.000 --> 00:11:23.430
But it also has that kind of
connotation of what the app does

00:11:23.430 --> 00:11:25.000
because it's got the Twitter bird.

00:11:25.000 --> 00:11:27.410
And I think it turned out really nicely.

00:11:29.660 --> 00:11:32.310
works well with all the different
sizes and that's one of the most

00:11:32.310 --> 00:11:35.100
important things for an app icon.

00:11:35.180 --> 00:11:37.690
And this is a technique, you know,
focusing on a single element

00:11:37.700 --> 00:11:40.760
rather than just taking your logo,
that a lot of companies have

00:11:40.970 --> 00:11:42.200
done in their app icons.

00:11:42.200 --> 00:11:45.120
So you can see some of these brands,
many of you are probably

00:11:45.120 --> 00:11:47.000
familiar with these brands.

00:11:47.040 --> 00:11:50.540
They didn't just take these recognizable
logos and put it into an app icon.

00:11:50.610 --> 00:11:54.020
They really highlighted some, you know,
single area of their

00:11:54.020 --> 00:11:58.800
typeface or their kind of,
you know, trademark imagery.

00:11:59.150 --> 00:12:00.690
To really highlight their app icon.

00:12:00.700 --> 00:12:03.080
And so they still have that color
palette that's going to kind of call

00:12:03.160 --> 00:12:04.960
them out and have that branding element.

00:12:05.060 --> 00:12:07.990
But it's a much simpler shape, you know,
either a single letter or, you know,

00:12:08.000 --> 00:12:11.000
a simple shape that will work
well at all these different sizes.

00:12:11.020 --> 00:12:13.310
And that's so important.

00:12:14.370 --> 00:12:16.490
What about the type of app
icons where you're trying to

00:12:16.490 --> 00:12:17.860
represent a physical object?

00:12:17.950 --> 00:12:20.000
Well,
if you're doing that type of app icon,

00:12:20.000 --> 00:12:22.680
it's critical that you make
sure that you're accurately

00:12:22.680 --> 00:12:26.120
portraying the actual materials
that make up that physical object.

00:12:26.120 --> 00:12:28.440
You need to be really realistic here.

00:12:28.440 --> 00:12:31.580
So pay attention to the subtle
details and textures of fabric or

00:12:31.730 --> 00:12:35.450
wood or paper or metal or glass,
whatever you're trying to represent.

00:12:35.450 --> 00:12:37.890
Make sure that it looks really authentic.

00:12:37.940 --> 00:12:40.870
And so you need to be careful
when you're building these types

00:12:40.870 --> 00:12:44.180
of app icons that you're not
just applying the standard gloss.

00:12:44.200 --> 00:12:58.470
You need to be careful when
you're building these types of

00:12:58.520 --> 00:13:14.180
app icons that you're not just
applying the standard gloss.

00:13:14.180 --> 00:13:14.180
And so when you apply this gloss
to these built-in app icons

00:13:14.180 --> 00:13:14.180
that we have on the device,
you can kind of see that actual

00:13:14.180 --> 00:13:14.180
object kind of isn't as strong
of a visual element anymore.

00:13:14.180 --> 00:13:14.180
It's just a little bit distracting.

00:13:14.180 --> 00:13:14.180
So make sure that if you
are building your app icon,

00:13:14.180 --> 00:13:14.180
you're really paying attention
to make sure that the gloss is

00:13:14.180 --> 00:13:14.180
adding value to the actual image.

00:13:14.180 --> 00:13:14.180
And turning off the gloss is as simple as
just checking that pre-rendered checkbox

00:13:14.180 --> 00:13:14.180
in the project summary tab of Xcode.

00:13:14.180 --> 00:13:14.180
And then when you submit that gloss,
you can see that it's actually

00:13:14.180 --> 00:13:14.180
adding value to the actual image.

00:13:14.180 --> 00:13:16.680
submit the icon,
we know not to apply that gloss,

00:13:16.680 --> 00:13:18.900
and everything will look great.

00:13:19.220 --> 00:13:22.200
There are some app icons where you want
to have gloss where you still want to

00:13:22.200 --> 00:13:25.400
keep that checkbox selected in Xcode.

00:13:25.400 --> 00:13:27.640
These are the app icons where you're
trying to represent a physical

00:13:27.640 --> 00:13:30.700
object or you're trying to do
something where you selectively want

00:13:30.700 --> 00:13:32.760
to apply gloss to the actual image.

00:13:32.760 --> 00:13:37.090
And so you actually bake in that
gloss when you're actually creating

00:13:37.090 --> 00:13:42.200
the app icon in Photoshop or whatever
image editing tool you're using.

00:13:42.200 --> 00:13:44.280
So as you can see, for example,
the YouTube icon,

00:13:44.280 --> 00:13:47.290
there's gloss on just the
glass of the television,

00:13:47.300 --> 00:13:49.630
but on the wood it kind of
falls off because it just

00:13:49.630 --> 00:13:50.590
wouldn't make sense there.

00:13:50.680 --> 00:13:53.120
And that's the same thing that
we've done with all these other app

00:13:53.120 --> 00:13:55.020
icons that we've created as well.

00:13:55.100 --> 00:13:57.180
So really make sure that you're
being true to the materials and

00:13:57.180 --> 00:14:00.300
really make sure you're not getting
distracted by some of the things

00:14:00.300 --> 00:14:04.460
like reflections and shadows that
make up a really great app icon.

00:14:04.530 --> 00:14:07.400
So the last tip I have on app
icons is just to have fun.

00:14:07.400 --> 00:14:08.220
Be creative.

00:14:08.220 --> 00:14:11.320
So developers, you guys have come up with
some amazing app icons.

00:14:11.320 --> 00:14:13.780
And, you know,
I just want to highlight some of them.

00:14:13.780 --> 00:14:13.860
I'm going to show you a few of them.

00:14:13.860 --> 00:14:15.640
One of my favorites here.

00:14:15.640 --> 00:14:17.090
This is Route C Pro.

00:14:17.100 --> 00:14:18.450
This is a great app icon.

