Here's Evernote food.

00:14:44.910 --> 00:14:48.040
This is a great app that
made a plate of sushi.

00:14:48.040 --> 00:14:50.340
Really creative use of this
rounded rectangle space.

00:14:50.420 --> 00:14:51.950
They really kind of
thought out of the box,

00:14:51.950 --> 00:14:52.550
if you will.

00:14:52.560 --> 00:14:55.680
And to go with the plate of sushi,
I thought I'd show you a

00:14:55.680 --> 00:14:57.450
mug of beer from Brewski Me.

00:14:57.450 --> 00:14:59.010
And this is a gorgeous icon.

00:14:59.080 --> 00:15:01.600
Again, really great attention to detail.

00:15:01.600 --> 00:15:05.850
You can see all this condensation
on the actual mug and the foam.

00:15:06.060 --> 00:15:08.730
And with all these app icons,
really great stuff.

00:15:08.800 --> 00:15:11.700
And the reason that they work
well is not only that they're

00:15:11.700 --> 00:15:15.150
beautiful at this large size,
they actually do follow all of these tips

00:15:15.150 --> 00:15:18.950
that I went through earlier where they're
really highlighting just a few colors,

00:15:18.950 --> 00:15:20.120
a few simple shapes.

00:15:20.120 --> 00:15:24.400
And that's really important when
you're designing your app icon.

00:15:26.100 --> 00:18:46.100
[Transcript missing]

00:18:46.280 --> 00:18:49.330
So they wanted to kind of test it around
and then they did something more bold.

00:18:49.340 --> 00:18:50.650
They really wanted to stand out.

