Okay, so before I wrap up,
I just want to leave you

00:55:21.560 --> 00:55:22.640
with some final thoughts.

00:55:22.640 --> 00:55:26.780
So like I said earlier,
there's a lot of information

00:55:26.780 --> 00:55:27.980
that's come up this week.

00:55:28.040 --> 00:55:32.110
I hope you've had a chance to
learn all the greatest new tips

00:55:32.110 --> 00:55:36.410
and tricks to really get your
apps kind of performing better,

00:55:36.410 --> 00:55:40.060
to make all the technology
just feel wonderful.

00:55:40.320 --> 00:55:44.320
And we've put a lot of work into
our platform to make it really

00:55:44.320 --> 00:55:46.300
easy for you to build apps.

00:55:46.300 --> 00:55:49.420
And so you'll hear from a lot of
people this week and a lot of just

00:55:49.420 --> 00:55:52.960
people when you're talking about
iOS in general after this week that,

00:55:52.960 --> 00:55:55.300
you know,
designing an iPhone or an iPad app,

00:55:55.300 --> 00:55:56.450
it's really easy.

00:55:56.500 --> 00:55:57.700
It's an easy thing to do.

00:55:57.730 --> 00:55:58.780
And that's true.

00:55:58.780 --> 00:56:01.210
We think it is the easiest
platform to design an app for.

00:56:01.220 --> 00:56:06.820
But the truth is designing a
great app is extremely difficult.

00:56:06.820 --> 00:56:10.300
And the reason why designing a
great app is extremely difficult.

00:56:10.320 --> 00:56:14.010
It's not because of some of the
stuff that we've covered this week.

00:56:14.050 --> 00:56:16.720
It's not about, you know,
the coding techniques or the different

00:56:16.720 --> 00:56:18.360
APIs or the different frameworks.

00:56:18.380 --> 00:56:22.260
It's not even about most of the different
UI tips that I've gone through today

00:56:22.260 --> 00:56:26.320
or all the great resources that we
have in the human interface guidelines.

00:56:26.320 --> 00:56:29.090
The reason designing a great app
is hard is because of all those

00:56:29.090 --> 00:56:31.970
different decisions you're going
to need to make throughout the

00:56:32.190 --> 00:56:35.610
process and getting agreement by the
different team members that you have.

00:56:35.660 --> 00:56:40.060
And so you really want to make sure
that you're spending all of your time.

00:56:40.350 --> 00:56:41.850
Focusing your efforts.

00:56:41.920 --> 00:56:46.070
You want to determine just the essential
features in your app and really spend all

00:56:46.070 --> 00:56:48.470
of your time just polishing those bits.

00:56:48.480 --> 00:56:51.100
When you try to do too
many things in your app,

00:56:51.170 --> 00:56:54.000
you're just not going to
set yourself up for success.

00:56:54.020 --> 00:56:58.130
Now, I can't think of any app on the app
store that is successful because it's

00:56:58.130 --> 00:57:00.440
got more features than everybody else.

00:57:00.520 --> 00:57:02.740
But I can think of the
most successful apps.

00:57:02.830 --> 00:57:05.800
And when I look at them,
it's because they made the hard decisions

00:57:05.800 --> 00:57:08.730
about what features not to include,
which users that aren't

00:57:08.730 --> 00:57:09.860
as important to them.

00:57:10.320 --> 00:57:14.580
They're the apps that really do one or
two things better than everybody else.

00:57:14.620 --> 00:57:17.400
And if you're able to do that,
if you're able to have just one

00:57:17.400 --> 00:57:20.750
thing or two things that are better
than every other app in that space,

00:57:20.810 --> 00:57:23.620
you're going to really set
yourself up for success.

00:57:23.620 --> 00:57:26.800
And then you'll be able to
build on that and add some of

00:57:26.800 --> 00:57:28.920
those features in app updates.

